WEBVTT

00:08.260 --> 00:13.020
CHAPTERS XI AND XII Of the Gospel According to St. Luke

00:13.020 --> 00:17.600
In the Authorized Version Commonly Known as the King James Translation

00:37.240 --> 00:44.420
And it came to pass, that as he was praying in a certain place, when he ceased, one of

00:44.420 --> 00:51.140
his disciples said unto him, Lord, teach us to pray, as John also taught his disciples.

00:52.300 --> 01:00.380
And he said unto them, When ye pray, say, Our Father which art in heaven, Hallowed be

01:00.380 --> 01:07.780
thy name, Thy kingdom come, thy will be done, as in heaven so in earth.

01:08.620 --> 01:16.840
Give us day by day our daily bread, and forgive us our sins, for we also forgive every one that

01:16.840 --> 01:23.560
is indebted to us, and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

01:25.480 --> 01:31.760
And he said unto them, Which of you shall have a friend, and shall go unto him at midnight,

01:32.140 --> 01:38.660
And say unto him, Friend, lend me three loaves, for a friend of mine in his journey has come

01:38.660 --> 01:41.340
to me, and I have nothing to set before him.

01:42.340 --> 01:48.420
And he from within shall answer and say, Trouble me not, the door is now shut, and my children

01:48.420 --> 01:51.520
are with me in bed, I cannot rise and give thee.

01:52.500 --> 01:59.020
I say unto you, Though he will not rise and give him because he is his friend, yet because

01:59.020 --> 02:04.200
of his importunity he will rise and give him as many as he needeth.

02:05.040 --> 02:13.780
And I say unto you, Ask, and it shall be given you, seek, and ye shall find, knock, and it

02:13.780 --> 02:16.000
shall be opened unto you.

02:16.520 --> 02:23.000
For every one that asketh receiveth, and he that seeketh findeth, and to him that knocketh,

02:23.280 --> 02:24.360
it shall be opened.

02:26.100 --> 02:31.660
If a son shall ask bread of any of you that is a father, will he give him a stone?

02:32.460 --> 02:36.720
Or if he ask a fish, will he for a fish give him a serpent?

02:37.640 --> 02:41.640
Or if he shall ask an egg, will he offer him a scorpion?

02:42.600 --> 02:48.940
If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall

02:48.940 --> 02:53.180
your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to them that ask him?

02:55.540 --> 03:01.920
And he was casting out a devil, and it was dumb, and it came to pass when the devil was

03:01.920 --> 03:05.220
gone out, the dumb spake, and the people wondered.

03:06.160 --> 03:12.980
But some of them said, He casteth out devils through bales above the chief of the devils,

03:13.760 --> 03:17.320
and others tempting him sought of him a sign from heaven.

03:17.320 --> 03:24.920
But he, knowing their thoughts, said unto them, Every kingdom divided against itself

03:24.920 --> 03:29.840
is brought to desolation, and a house divided against a house falleth.

03:30.720 --> 03:35.920
If Satan also be divided against himself, how shall his kingdom stand?

03:36.960 --> 03:40.080
Because ye say that I cast out devils through bales above.

03:40.800 --> 03:46.080
And if I by bales above cast out devils, by whom do your sons cast them out?

03:46.820 --> 03:48.540
Therefore shall they be your judges.

03:49.860 --> 03:56.520
But if I with the finger of God cast out devils, no doubt the kingdom of God is come upon you.

03:57.680 --> 04:02.420
When a strong man armed keepeth his palace, his goods are in peace.

04:02.940 --> 04:09.000
But when a stronger than he shall come upon him, and overcome him, he taketh from him

04:09.000 --> 04:13.540
all his armor wherein he trusted, and divideth his spoils.

04:14.500 --> 04:20.800
He that is not with me is against me, and he that gathereth not with me scattereth.

04:22.480 --> 04:27.920
When the unclean spirit is gone out of a man, he walketh through dry places seeking rest,

04:28.280 --> 04:33.140
and finding none he saith, I will return unto my house whence I came out.

04:33.900 --> 04:37.580
And when he cometh, he findeth it swept and garnished.

04:37.580 --> 04:43.660
Then goeth he, and taketh to him seven other spirits more wicked than himself.

04:44.680 --> 04:51.100
And they enter in, and dwell there, and the last state of that man is worse than the first.

04:54.060 --> 05:00.320
And it came to pass, as he spake these things, a certain woman of the company lifted up her voice,

05:00.420 --> 05:06.200
and said unto him, Blessed is the womb that bare thee, and the paps which thou hast sucked.

05:07.320 --> 05:13.980
But he said, Yea, rather blessed are they that hear the word of God, and keep it.

05:16.320 --> 05:23.720
And when the people were gathered thick together, he began to say, This is an evil generation.

05:24.320 --> 05:30.600
They seek a sign, and there shall no sign be given it but the sign of Jonas the prophet.

05:31.240 --> 05:39.280
For as Jonas was a sign unto the Ninevites, so shall also the Son of Man be to this generation.

05:40.420 --> 05:45.220
The Queen of the South shall rise up in the judgment with the men of this generation,

05:45.600 --> 05:51.560
and condemn them. For she came from the utmost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon,

05:52.020 --> 05:58.980
and behold a greater than Solomon is here. The men of Nineveh shall rise up in the judgment

05:58.980 --> 06:04.460
with this generation, and shall condemn it. For they repented at the preaching of Jonas,

06:04.880 --> 06:12.140
and behold a greater than Jonas is here. No man when he hath lighted a candle putteth it in a

06:12.140 --> 06:19.120
secret place, neither under a bushel, but on a candlestick, that they which come in may see the

06:19.120 --> 06:27.120
light. The light of the body is the eye. Therefore when thine eye is single, thy whole body also is

06:27.120 --> 06:34.860
full of light. But when thine eye is evil, thy body also is full of darkness. Take heed therefore

06:34.860 --> 06:42.080
that the light which is in thee be not darkness. If thy whole body therefore be full of light,

06:42.320 --> 06:48.240
having no part dark, the whole shall be full of light, as when the bright shining of a candle

06:51.520 --> 06:59.440
And as he spake, a certain Pharisee besought him to dine with him, and he went in, and sat down to

06:59.440 --> 07:06.800
meet. And when the Pharisees saw it, he marvelled that he had not first washed before dinner. And

07:06.800 --> 07:13.160
the Lord said unto him, Now do ye Pharisees make clean the outside of the cup and the platter,

07:13.160 --> 07:20.420
But your inward part is full of ravening and wickedness. Ye fools, did not he that made that

07:20.420 --> 07:27.220
which is without make that which is within also? But rather give alms of such things as ye have,

07:27.580 --> 07:33.760
and behold all things are clean unto you. But woe unto you Pharisees, for ye tithe the

07:33.760 --> 07:39.820
minth and rue and all manner of herbs, and pass over judgment and the love of God. These ought

07:39.820 --> 07:46.920
ye to have done, and not to leave the other undone. Woe unto you Pharisees, for ye love

07:46.920 --> 07:52.980
the uppermost seats in the synagogues and greetings in the markets. Woe unto you scribes

07:52.980 --> 08:00.020
and Pharisees, hypocrites, for ye are as graves which appear not, and the men that walk over them

08:00.020 --> 08:07.900
are not aware of them. Then answered one of the lawyers, and said unto him, Master, thus saying

08:07.900 --> 08:16.060
thou reproaches us also. And he said, Woe unto you also ye lawyers, for ye laid men with burdens,

08:16.200 --> 08:23.320
grievous to be born, and ye yourselves touch not the burdens with one of your fingers. Woe unto you,

08:23.420 --> 08:29.580
for ye build the sepulchres of the prophets, and your fathers kill them. Truly ye bear witness that

08:29.580 --> 08:35.500
ye allow the deeds of your fathers, for they indeed kill them, and ye build their sepulchres.

08:36.400 --> 08:43.240
Therefore also said the Wisdom of God, I will send them prophets and apostles, and some of them

08:43.240 --> 08:49.700
they shall slay and persecute. That the blood of all the prophets which was shed from the foundation

08:49.700 --> 08:56.240
of the world may be required of this generation. From the blood of Abel unto the blood of Zacharias,

08:56.680 --> 09:03.040
which perished between the altar and the temple, verily I say unto you, it shall be required of

09:03.040 --> 09:09.840
this generation. Woe unto you lawyers, for ye have taken away the key of knowledge. Ye entered

09:09.840 --> 09:18.080
not in yourselves, and them that were entering in ye hindered. And as he said these things unto them,

09:18.460 --> 09:23.980
the scribes and the Pharisees began to urge him vehemently, and to provoke him to speak of

09:23.980 --> 09:29.920
many things, laying wait for him, and seeking to catch something out of his mouth that they

09:29.920 --> 09:39.800
might accuse him. Chapter 12 In the meantime, when there were gathered together an innumerable

09:39.800 --> 09:46.880
multitude of people, insomuch that they trod one upon another, he began to say unto his disciples,

09:47.020 --> 09:54.480
first of all, Beware ye of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy. For there is

09:54.480 --> 10:01.800
nothing covered that shall not be revealed, neither hid that shall not be known. Therefore

10:01.800 --> 10:08.420
whatsoever ye have spoken in darkness shall be heard in the light, and that which ye have spoken

10:08.420 --> 10:15.880
in the ear, in closets, shall be proclaimed upon the housetops. And I say unto you, my friends,

10:16.240 --> 10:22.940
be not afraid of them that kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do. But I

10:22.940 --> 10:29.740
will forewarn you whom ye shall fear. Fear him which after he hath killed hath power to cast

10:29.740 --> 10:37.580
you into hell. Yea, I say unto you, fear him. Are not five sparrows sold for two farthings,

10:38.280 --> 10:44.420
and not one of them is forgotten before God? But even the very hairs of your head are all numbered.

10:45.300 --> 10:52.400
Fear not, therefore, ye are of more value than many sparrows. Also I say unto you,

10:52.540 --> 10:59.440
Whosoever shall confess me before men, him shall the Son of Man also confess before the angels of

10:59.440 --> 11:06.740
God. But he that denieth me before men shall be denied before the angels of God. And whosoever

11:06.740 --> 11:13.320
shall speak a word against the Son of Man, it shall be forgiven him. But unto him that blasphemeth

11:13.320 --> 11:20.320
against the Holy Ghost, it shall not be forgiven. And when they bring you unto the synagogues,

11:20.560 --> 11:26.580
and unto magistrates and powers, take ye no thought how or what thing ye shall answer,

11:26.900 --> 11:33.280
or what ye shall say. For the Holy Ghost shall teach you in the same hour what ye ought to say.

11:34.880 --> 11:41.300
And one of the companies said unto him, Master, speak to my brother that he divide the inheritance

11:41.300 --> 11:50.800
with me. And he said unto him, Man, who made me a judge or divider over you? And he said unto them,

11:51.220 --> 11:57.520
Take heed, and beware of covetousness, for a man's life consisteth not in the abundance

11:57.520 --> 12:04.900
of the things which he possesseth. And he spake a parable unto them, saying, The ground of a certain

12:04.900 --> 12:11.800
rich man brought forth plentifully. And he thought within himself, saying, What shall I do,

12:11.980 --> 12:19.120
because I have no room where to bestow my fruits? And he said, This I will do, I will pull down my

12:19.120 --> 12:26.780
barns and build greater, and there will I bestow all my fruits and my goods. And I will say to my

12:26.780 --> 12:33.940
soul, Soul, thou hast much goods laid up for many years, take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry.

12:34.900 --> 12:41.520
But God said unto him, Thou fool, this night thy soul shall be required of thee,

12:42.120 --> 12:45.900
then whose shall those things be which thou hast provided?

12:47.160 --> 12:52.880
So is he that layeth up treasure for himself, and is not rich toward God.

12:54.620 --> 13:01.340
And he said unto his disciples, Therefore I say unto you, Take no thought for your life,

13:01.340 --> 13:09.500
what ye shall eat, neither for the body, what ye shall put on. The life is more than meat,

13:09.880 --> 13:16.380
and the body is more than raiment. Consider the ravens, for they neither sow nor reap,

13:17.000 --> 13:23.460
which neither have storehouse nor barn, and God feedeth them. How much more are ye better

13:23.460 --> 13:30.280
than the fowls? And which of you, with taking thought, can add to his stature one cubit?

13:30.840 --> 13:36.840
If ye then be not able to do that thing which is least, why take ye thought for the rest?

13:38.020 --> 13:46.320
Consider the lilies, how they grow, they toil not, they spin not. And yet I say unto you,

13:46.640 --> 13:50.480
that Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.

13:51.720 --> 13:58.760
If then God so clothe the grass, which is today in the field and tomorrow is cast into the oven,

13:59.400 --> 14:07.280
how much more will he clothe you, O ye of little faith? And seek not ye what ye shall eat or what

14:07.280 --> 14:14.240
ye shall drink, neither be ye of doubtful mind. For all these things do the nations of the world

14:14.240 --> 14:21.560
seek after, and your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things. But rather seek ye the kingdom

14:21.560 --> 14:30.320
of God, and all these things shall be added unto you. Fear not, little flock, for it is your

14:30.320 --> 14:37.760
Father's good pleasure to give you the kingdom. Sell that ye have, and give alms, provide yourselves

14:37.760 --> 14:44.720
bags which wax not old, a treasure in the heavens that faileth not, where no thief approacheth,

14:44.720 --> 14:51.520
neither moth corrupteth. For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.

14:53.340 --> 14:59.880
Let your loins be girded about, and your lights burning. And ye yourselves like unto men that

14:59.880 --> 15:05.660
wait for their Lord, when he will return from the wedding, that when he cometh and knocketh,

15:05.880 --> 15:12.360
they may open unto him immediately. Blessed are those servants whom the Lord, when he cometh,

15:12.360 --> 15:19.520
shall find watching. Verily I say unto you that he shall gird himself and make them to sit down

15:19.520 --> 15:25.960
to meet, and will come forth and serve them. And if he shall come in the second watch,

15:26.260 --> 15:31.260
or come in the third watch, and find them so, blessed are those servants.

15:32.660 --> 15:38.360
And this know, that if the goodman of the house had known what hour the thief would come,

15:38.360 --> 15:42.820
he would have watched, and not have suffered his house to be broken through.

15:44.040 --> 15:50.420
Be therefore ready also, for the Son of Man cometh at an hour, when ye think not.

15:51.940 --> 15:59.180
Then Peter said unto him, Lord, speakest thou this parable unto us, or even to all?

16:00.080 --> 16:06.600
And the Lord said, Who then is that faithful and wise steward, whom his Lord shall make ruler over

16:06.600 --> 16:13.160
his household, to give them their portion of meat in due season? Blessed is that servant whom his

16:13.160 --> 16:20.400
Lord, when he cometh, shall find so doing. Of a truth I say unto you, that he will make him ruler

16:20.400 --> 16:28.300
over all that he hath. But, and if that servant say in his heart, My Lord delayeth his coming,

16:28.720 --> 16:34.060
and shall begin to beat the men's servants and maidens, and to eat and to drink and to be drunken,

16:34.060 --> 16:40.400
the Lord of that servant will come in a day when he looketh not for him, and at an hour when he is

16:40.400 --> 16:45.800
not aware, and will cut him in sunder, and will appoint him his portion with the unbelievers.

16:47.120 --> 16:53.200
And that servant which knew his Lord's will, and prepared not himself, neither did according to his

16:53.200 --> 17:00.460
will, shall be beaten with many stripes. But he that knew not, and did not commit things worthy

17:00.460 --> 17:08.860
of stripes, shall be beaten with few stripes. For unto whomsoever much is given, of him shall

17:08.860 --> 17:15.580
be much required. And to whom men have committed much, of him they will ask the more.

17:17.140 --> 17:23.020
I am come to send fire on the earth, and what will I if it be already kindled?

17:23.780 --> 17:30.120
But I have a baptism to be baptized with, and how am I straightened till it be accomplished?

17:31.020 --> 17:36.500
Suppose ye that I am come to give peace on earth, I tell you nay, but rather division.

17:37.560 --> 17:43.520
For from henceforth there shall be five in one house, divided three against two, and two against

17:43.520 --> 17:49.420
three. The father shall be divided against the son, and the son against the father, the mother

17:49.420 --> 17:54.620
against the daughter, and the daughter against the mother, the mother-in-law against her daughter-in-law,

17:54.620 --> 17:59.840
and the daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law. And he said also to the people,

18:00.380 --> 18:07.800
When ye see a cloud rise out of the west, straightway ye say, There cometh a shower, and so it is.

18:08.420 --> 18:15.580
And when ye see the south wind blow, ye say, There will be heat, and it cometh to pass. Ye

18:15.580 --> 18:21.780
hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky and of the earth, but how is it that ye do not

18:21.780 --> 18:28.260
discern this time? Yea, and why even of yourselves judge ye not what is right?

18:29.940 --> 18:35.080
When thou goest with thine adversary to the magistrate, as thou art in the way,

18:35.280 --> 18:40.500
give diligence that thou mayest be delivered from him, lest he hail thee to the judge,

18:40.900 --> 18:45.380
and the judge deliver thee to the officer, and the officer cast thee into prison.

18:45.380 --> 18:52.690
I tell thee, thou shalt not depart thence, till thou hast paid the very last might.

18:54.440 --> 18:58.840
CHAPTERS XI AND XII OF THE GOSPEL ACCORDING TO ST. LUKE

18:58.840 --> 19:03.520
IN THE AUTHORIZED VERSION, COMMONLY KNOWN AS THE KING JAMES TRANSLATION

19:03.520 --> 19:09.380
READING BY FATHER ZILEY OF DETROIT, OCTOBER 2008

